definition: classifier for gifts, newspaper, magazine, papers, reports, contracts etc/variant of 分[fen4]

sentences.english: In May, we reported about a new album from singer Josh Groban.
sentences.chinese: 五月份，我們報道過一張喬許葛洛班的新專輯。

sentences.english: The offering is part of a two-month trial that would begin in May.
sentences.chinese: 在線播放將有兩個月的測試期，從五月份開始。

sentences.english: Because It's very hot in summer in Beihai, so I have buy a fan to got the cool!
sentences.chinese: 因爲五月份天氣比較熱，所以，新買了一臺的電風扇。

sentences.english: After many discussions, Kanzius filed for a patent in May.
sentences.chinese: 經過多次討論後，肯茲尤斯於五月份申請了專利。

sentences.english: Please ship the goods in one lot in May.
sentences.chinese: 請在五月份將貨物分一批運過來。

sentences.english: As one local resident put it in May, "By day there is government.
sentences.chinese: 正如一位當地居民在五月份對它的描述”白天有政府。

sentences.english: Brown returned to his family home in Fife after losing the election in May.
sentences.chinese: 五月份選舉失利後，布朗就回到他的家鄉法夫。

sentences.english: A new one, “Two Belles in Love,” opened in Beijing in May.
sentences.chinese: 新排崑劇《憐香伴》，五月份在北京首演。

sentences.english: Since May, very few foreigners have checked in.
sentences.chinese: 五月份以來，登記入住的外國人很少。

sentences.english: Released in May, it's viewed 4 million times at www.tudou.com.
sentences.chinese: 該電影五月份發佈，在土豆網上被點擊了400萬次。

sentences.english: Preparations are well under way for a week of special events in May.
sentences.chinese: 五月份特別活動周的準備工作正在順利展開。

sentences.english: They met in May and became lovers soon after.
sentences.chinese: 他們在五月份相遇，不久就成爲了情侶。

sentences.english: Bank loans fell 25 percent in May from April.
sentences.chinese: 四月份到五月份，銀行貸款下降了25%。

sentences.english: In May a new waterworks will go into operation.
sentences.chinese: 五月份，一座新的自來水廠將投入使用。

sentences.english: Since last May, Sino-Indian relations have been undermined.
sentences.chinese: 去年五月份以後，中印關係受到了損害。
